summary:
The Security Council,

Recalling previous resolutions on Côte d'Ivoire and the subregion, 

Decides to authorize the Secretary-General to extend until 30 September 2011 the redeployment from UNMIL to UNOCI of three armed helicopters with crews;

Requests the Secretary-General to provide an updated analysis and recommendations on inter-mission cooperation arrangements by 15 September 2011;

Decides to extend the deployment of an additional 2,000 military personnel to UNOCI and temporary additional military and police capabilities until 31 July 2011;

Requests the support of troop- and police-contributing countries;

Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
